article.description: Isaiah Walton had 22 points and Longwood scored the game's final 14 points to overtake Liberty 58-51 on Friday night.
article.headline: Longwood scores final 14 points to beat Liberty 58-51
article.linkText: Longwood scores final 14 points to beat Liberty 58-51
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Isaiah Walton had 22 points and Longwood scored the game's final 14 points to overtake Liberty 58-51 on Friday night. Walton and Charles Glover scored five points each and Spencer Franklin four in the game-ending rally for the Lancers (5-13, 2/3 Big South). Lovell Cabbil opened the second half with a basket that put Liberty up by 10 before Walton scored nine points in a 14-4 run to tie. Georgie Pacheco-Ortiz's jumper with 3:08 to go gave Liberty a 51-44 lead, but the Flames (12-6, 3-2) missed their final five shots while the Lancers hit their final four. Cabbil scored 10 points for the Flames, who made just 4 of 18 from the arc in having a three-game win streak snapped. Liberty built a 12-point lead in the first half before Longwood cut it to 28-20 at the break.
